# ADR-0047 — ask a scene VLM (e.g. Qwen3.5-4B NF4, kind: "vlm") an open-ended
# question about the CURRENT camera view, on demand.
#
# Called by the reasoner's read-only `query_scene` tool dispatch
# (openral_reasoner_ros.reasoner_node._dispatch_query_scene). The perception
# node (openral_perception_ros.ros_image_detector_node) captures the latest
# frame of the requested camera and forwards it plus the question to the VLM
# sidecar, returning the model's free-text answer. Read-only: no actuation.
#
# Unlike LocateInView (which localizes an object and returns boxes), this
# answers open-ended scene-state questions for the reasoner's replanning ladder
# — task progress and success/failure verification ("has the robot grasped the
# mug?", "is the bowl on the shelf?", "did we drop the object?").
#
# Request:
#   question — free-text question about the scene's state. Sent verbatim to the
#              VLM as the textual prompt alongside the frame.
#   camera   — optional camera selector. Empty = the perception node's
#              primary/default camera; otherwise one of its configured camera
#              ids so the reasoner can choose a viewpoint. NOT a hardcoded name.
#
# Response:
#   ok      — true iff the VLM produced an answer (a frame was available and the
#             sidecar responded). False on no-frame / sidecar error.
#   camera  — the camera id actually queried (echoes the resolved default).
#   answer  — the VLM's free-text answer when ok; empty string otherwise.

string question
string camera
---
bool ok
string camera
string answer
